"Pseudo Random Distribution" are used in various games to make the RNG
less likely to go on long runs of hits or misses. a RNG with more fibre
in its diet, in other words

    % make prd-trial
    gcc -std=c99 -O3 prd-trial.c -o prd-trial
    % ./prd-trial | r-fu summary
    elements 1000 mean 0.246 range 0.005 min 0.243 max 0.248 sd 0.001

         0%     25%     50%     75%    100%
    0.24336 0.24528 0.24580 0.24630 0.24797

however a comparison of this ~25% odds with a regular 25% test shows
that the PRD is less likely to go on runs of misses

    % make prd
    gcc   prd.o   -o prd
    % ./prd | r-fu colsumm - prd regular
                    prd     regular
    Count   1000.000000 1000.000000
    Range     15.000000   30.000000
    Mean      15.941000   28.615000
    Sdev       2.834352    4.536447
    Min.      13.000000   19.000000
    1st Qu.   14.000000   26.000000
    Median    14.000000   28.000000
    3rd Qu.   18.000000   31.000000
    Max.      28.000000   49.000000
